This folder contains the data and results for experiments comparing with other methods. The purpose is to present the efficiency of the LBBDA method.

We test our proposed LBBDA over instances from Michels 2019. (A benders’ decomposition algorithm with combinatorial cuts for the multi-manned assembly line balancing problem. European Journal of Operational Research, 278 (3), 796–808). This is the simple multi-manned ALBP where workers are homogeneous and each task requires exactly one worker to execute, without zone-incompatible tasks.

The filenames are structured as: "filename_cycle_maxworkers" where maxworkers refers to the max number of workers per station.
